{"lexicon" 1, "id" "com.etzhayyim.hinagata.clause", "description" "A reusable clause in the hinagata 雛形 commons (per ADR-2606111954) — a building block shared across templates (the cross-template backbone). A clause declares its drafting role and its DISCLOSED optionality (mandatory / recommended / optional), where `mandatory` means a cited statute requires the clause — a DISCLOSED structural fact sourced from the instrument, never a hinagata verdict (N3). Statute bindings are recorded separately in `com.etzhayyim.hinagata.statuteCitation`.", "defs" {"main" {"type" "record", "key" "tid", "record" {"type" "object", "required" ["clauseId" "label" "role" "optionality"], "properties" {"clauseId" {"type" "string", "description" "Stable hinagata id, e.g. `cl.confidentiality`.", "maxLength" 128}, "label" {"type" "string", "description" "Human label, e.g. \"Confidentiality / non-disclosure\".", "maxLength" 256}, "role" {"type" "string", "description" "Drafting role of the clause.", "enum" ["definitions" "recitals" "payment" "term" "termination" "confidentiality" "ip-assignment" "ip-license" "warranty" "liability" "indemnity" "governing-law" "dispute" "privacy" "data-rights" "force-majeure" "no-interest" "cooling-off" "signature" "boilerplate"]}, "optionality" {"type" "string", "description" "DISCLOSED — `mandatory` (a cited statute requires this clause), `recommended`, or `optional`. Sourced from the instrument, never a hinagata opinion (N3).", "enum" ["mandatory" "recommended" "optional"]}, "concept" {"type" "string", "description" "Controlled legal concept the clause instantiates, e.g. `data-protection`.", "maxLength" 128}, "bodyCid" {"type" "string", "format" "cid", "description" "Optional IPFS CIDv1 of the clause's canonical text fragment (content-addressed, reusable)."}}}}}}
